# nl-rag distilled facts — domain: airdrie-north-lanarkshire
# one declarative sentence per line; load with:  neuron --db app.db import pack.facts --scope knowledge
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] This is a complete **list of acts of the Parliament of the United Kingdom for the year 1821**.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] Note that the first parliament of the United Kingdom was held in 1801; parliaments between 1707 and 1800 were either parliaments of Great Britain or of Ireland).
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] For acts passed up until 1707, see the list of acts of the Parliament of England and the list of acts of the Parliament of Scotland.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] For acts passed from 1707 to 1800, see the list of acts of the Parliament of Great Britain.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] See also the list of acts of the Parliament of Ireland.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] For acts of the devolved parliaments and assemblies in the United Kingdom, see the list of acts of the Scottish Parliament, the list of acts of the Northern Ireland Assembly, and the list of acts and measures of Senedd Cymru; see also the list of acts of the Parliament of Northern Ireland.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] The number shown after each act's title is its chapter number.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] Acts passed before 1963 are cited using this number, preceded by the year(s) of the reign during which the relevant parliamentary session was held; thus the Union with Ireland Act 1800 is cited as "39 & 40 Geo.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] 67", meaning the 67th act passed during the session that started in the 39th year of the reign of George III and which finished in the 40th year of that reign.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] Note that the modern convention is to use Arabic numerals in citations (thus "41 Geo.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] Acts of the last session of the Parliament of Great Britain and the first session of the Parliament of the United Kingdom are both cited as "41 Geo.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] Acts passed from 1963 onwards are simply cited by calendar year and chapter number.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] All modern acts have a short title, e.g. the Local Government Act 2003.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] Some earlier acts also have a short title given to them by later acts, such as by the Short Titles Act 1896.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] The second session of the 7th Parliament of the United Kingdom, which met from 23 January 1821 until 11 July 1821.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] This session was also traditionally cited as **1 & 2 G.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An act for enabling His Majesty to make Provision for Her Majesty the Queen.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] for more effectually discovering the Longitude at Sea, and encouraging Attempts to find a Northern Passage between the Atlantic and Pacific Oceans, and to approach the Northern Pole.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An act for continuing to His Majesty certain Duties on Malt, Sugar, Tobacco and Snuff, Foreign Spirits and Sweets, in Great Britain; and on Pensions, Offices and Personal Estates in England; for the Service of the Year one thousand eight hundred and twenty one.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act for applying certain Monies therein mentioned for the service of the Year one thousand eight hundred and twenty one.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to continue for Two Years from the passing thereof, to the End of the then next Session of Parliament, the several Acts for the Transportation of Offenders from Great Britain.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] to allow the Importation into certain Ports in Nova Scotia and New Brunswick, of certain enumerated Articles and the Re-exportation thereof from such Ports.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] for staying Proceedings against any Governor or other Persons concerned in imposing and levying Duties in New South Wales; for continuing certain Duties; and for empowering the said Governor to levy a Duty on Spirits made in the said Colony.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act for punishing Mutiny and Desertion; and for the better Payment of the Army and their Quarters.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act for the regulating of His Majesty's Royal Marine Forces while on Shore.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to continue until the Twenty fifth Day of March One thousand eight hundred and twenty four, the Bounties on the Exportation of certain Silk Manufactures, and the Duties on the Importation of Buck Wheat.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] for the More effectual Encouragement of the Manufacture of Flax and Cotton in Great Britain.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] to continue certain Laws of Excise with regard to Crown Glass, and Flint and Phial Glass, and to alter certain Laws with regard to Flint Glass.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] for the free Importation of Cochineal and Indigo.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to authorize the Transfer of Stocks and Payment of Dividends of Lunatics residing out of England.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act for further facilitating the Despatch of Business in the Court of King's Bench.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to explain and amend an Act of the Parliament of Ireland, passed in the Seventh Year of the Reign of His Majesty King George the Second, for better regulating the Payment of Fees of Attornies and Solicitors, and other Purposes therein mentioned.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to repeal an Act, made in the Parliament of Ireland in the Twenty eighth Year of the Reign of Queen Elizabeth, against Witchcraft and Sorcery.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to permit the Removal of certain Goods from Great Britain to Ireland, and from Ireland to Great Britain, by Cocket, Certificate, Let Pass or Transire.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to continue until the Fifth Day of April One thousand eight hundred and twenty three, several Acts of His late Majesty, for reducing the Duties payable on Horses used for the Purposes therein mentioned.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act for altering and amending the Laws of Excise for securing the Payment of the Duties on Beer and Ale brewed in Great Britain.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to amend the Law respecting the inclosing of Open Fields, Pastures, Moors, Commons and Waste Lands in England.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] to that part of the United Kingdom called Ireland.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act for fixing the Rates of Subsistence to be paid to Innkeepers and others on quartering Soldiers.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act for making further Provision for the gradual Resumption of Payments in Cash by the Bank of England.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act for making further Provision for the Resumption of Payments in Cash by the Bank of Ireland.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act for abolishing the African Company, and transferring to and vesting in His Majesty all the Forts, Possessions, and Property now belonging to or held by them.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to remove Doubts on the Allowances of the Duty paid on Irish Starch imported into Great Britain, payable on such Starch consumed in preparing Manu factures of Flax or Cotton in Great Britain, and for regulating the Importation thereof.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act for further improving the Roads between London and Holyhead, by Coventry, Birmingham and Shrewsbury.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act for removing Doubts as to the Continuance of the Hereditary Revenue in Scotland.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act for declaring valid certain Indentures of Apprenticeship, and Certificates of Settlements of poor Persons in England.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to make more effectual Provision for the Establishment of Asylums for the Lunatic Poor, and for the Custody of Insane Persons charged with Offences in Ireland.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] as inflicts Capital Punishment on Persons guilty of stealing to the Amount of Five Shillings out of or from Shops, Warehouses and other Outbuildings and Places, and to provide more suitable and effectual Punishment for such Offences.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act for the better Regulation of the Public Notaries in Ireland.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to repeal the Duties of Customs on the Importation into Great Britain of certain Sorts of Wood and Timber, and certain Drawbacks or Allowances in respect of such Duties, and to grant other Duties and Drawbacks in lieu thereof.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act for establishing Regulations respecting certain Parts, of the Proceedings in the Court of Session, and in the Court of Commissioners for Teinds, and respecting the Duties, Qualifications, and Emoluments of certain Clerks and other Officers of the said.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act for the better Regulation of the Courts of Admiralty in Scotland, and of certain Proceedings in the Court of Session connected therewith.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] for preventing Frauds committed by Bankrupts, as inflicts Capital Punishment on certain Offences therein specified; and to provide more suitable and effectual Punishment for such Offences.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act for giving greater facility in the Prosecution and abatement of Nuisances arising from Furnaces used and in the working of Steam Engines.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to defray, until the Twenty fifth Day of June One thousand eight hundred and twenty-two, the Charge of the Pay and Clothing of the Militia of Ireland; and for making Allowances to Officers and Quartermasters of the said Militia during Peace.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to exclude Persons holding certain Judicial Offices in Ireland, from being Members of the House of Commons.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] for consolidating and rendering more effectual the several Acts for the Purchase of Buildings, and further Improvement of the Street and Places near to West minster Hall and the Two Houses of Parliament.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to regulate the Attendance of Jurors at the Assizes in certain Cases.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An act to exclude the Borough of Grampound, in the County of Cornwall, from sending Burgesses to serve in Parliament; and to enable the County of York to send Two additional Knights to serve in Parliament, in lieu thereof.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to amend the several Acts for the Regulation of Attornies and Solicitors.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] relating to the Execution of Letters of Attorney and Wills of Petty Officers, Seamen and Marines, in His Majesty's Navy.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to improve the Land Revenues of the Crown, and of His Majesty's Duchy of Lancaster, and for making Provisions and Regulations for the better Management thereof.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to regulate the Proceedings in the Civil Side of the Court of King's Bench, and also in the Court of Common Pleas, and in the Pleas or Common Law Side of the Court of Exchequer in Ireland.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to regulate the Office of Clerk of Assize or Nisi Prius, or Judge's Registrar, in Ireland.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to remove Doubts as to the Amount of Stamp Duties to be paid on Deeds and other Instruments, under the several Acts in force in Great Britain and Ireland respectively.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] for the better Relief Employment of the Poor.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to regulate the Expences of Elections of Members to serve in Parliament for Ireland.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act for the Relief of Insolvent Debtors in Ireland.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act for exempting Ships in Ballast in the South Sea Trade from certain Tonnage Duties.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to regulate the Appropriation of unclaimed Shares of Prize Money belonging to Soldiers or Seamen in the Service of the East India Company.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to regulate the Times for holding the Sessions of the Peace, in the several Counties in Ireland.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to amend the Laws now in force relating to Vagrants, until the First Day of September One thousand eight hundred and twenty two.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act for the further Regulation of Trade to and from Places within the Limits of the Charter of the East India Company (except the Dominions of the Emperor of China), and Ports or Places beyond the Limits of the said Charter, belonging to any State or Country in Amity with His Majesty.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act for regulating the Fur Trade, and establishing a Criminal and Civil Jurisdiction within certain Parts of North America.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act for extending the Drawbacks on Coals used in Mines and Smelting Works within the Counties of Cornwall and Devon, and for allowing a Drawback of the Duties on Coals used in draining Coal Mines in the County of Pembroke.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to repeal so much of several Acts to prevent the excessive Price of Coals, as relates to Coal Yards established at the Expence of the Public in Dublin and Cork.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act for vesting all Estates and Property, occupied for the Ordnance Service, in the principal Officers of the Ordnance; and for granting certain Powers to the said principal Officers.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act for raising a Loan of Thirteen Millions from the Commissioners for the Reduction of the National Debt.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act for raising the Sum of Twenty nine Millions by Exchequer Bills, for the Service of the Year One thousand eight hundred and twenty one.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to establish an Agreement with the Governor and Company of the Bank of Ireland, for advancing the Sum of Five hundred thousand Pounds Irish Currency; and to empower the said Governor and Company to enlarge the Capital Stock or Fund of the said Bank to Three Millions.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to permit for Three Years, the Transfer from certain Public Stocks or Funds in Ireland, to certain Public Stocks or Funds in Great Britain.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] for regulating Payments to the Treasurer of the Navy under the Heads of Old Stores and Imprests, and to make other Provisions in lieu thereof.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to continue and amend certain Acts for preventing Frauds and Depredations committed on Merchants, Shipowners, and Underwriters, by Boatmen and others; and also for remedying certain Defects relative to the Adjustment of Salvage in England, under an Act made in the Twelfth Year of Queen Anne.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to abolish the Payment, by Prisoners in Ireland, of Gaol Fees, and all other Fees relating to the Commitment, Continuance, Trial or Discharge of such Prisoners, and to prevent Abuses by Gaolers, Bailiffs and other Officers.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to regulate Acceptances of Bills of Exchange.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to repeal certain Bounties granted for the Encouragement of the Deep Sea British White Herring Fishery, and to make further Regulations relating to the said Fishery.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act for raising the Sum of One Million British Currency, by Treasury Bills in Ireland, for the Service of the Year One thousand eight hundred and twenty.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] as requires a Registry of Wool sent Coastwise.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act for allowing to Distillers of Spirits for Home Consumption in Scotland, a Drawback of a Portion of the Duty on Malt used by them; and for the further Prevention of smuggling of Spirits on the Borders of Scotland and England.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act for further reducing until the Fifth Day of July One thousand eight hundred and twenty two, the Duty on Malt made from Bear or Bigg only, for Home Consumption in Scotland.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] for granting certain Duties of Customs in Great Britain.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to explain and amend several Acts relating the assessing, levying and collecting the County Rates.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] for enabling William Blackall Simonds Esquire, to sell or mortgage his Estate and Interest in the Impropriate Rectory of Caversham, in the County of Oxford, free from the Claims of the Crown.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] Years of His late Majesty King George the Third, for regulating the Importation and Exportation of Corn, Grain, Meal and Flour into and from Great Britain, and to make further Provisions in lieu thereof.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act for the Amendment of the Law of Rescue.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] as restrains the Proprietors of Wharfs between London Bridge and the Temple from erecting any Buildings or Enclosures thereon.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to appoint Commissioners for inquiring into the Collection and Management of the Revenue in Ireland, and the several Establishments connected therewith.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to grant certain Bounties on the Exportation of Stuffs made of Silk mixed with Mohair, and of Stuffs made of Mohair mixed with Worsted, the Manufacture of Great Britain or Ireland.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to authorize the Exchange of Lands, Tenements, or Hereditaments, subject to Trusts for Charitable Purposes, for other Lands, Tenements, or Hereditaments.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] Property Occupied for Naval Service, etc.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act for vesting all Estates and Property, occupied by or for the Naval Service of this Kingdom, in the principal Officers and Commissioners of His Majesty's Navy, and for granting certain Powers to the said principal Officers and Commissioners.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to regulate the Importation of Rum into Islands of Jersey, Guernsey, Alderney and Sark.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] for rendering the growing Produce of the Consolidated Fund of the United Kingdom, arising in Great Britain, available for the Public Service.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act for charging a Duty on British Spirits brought into certain Parts of the District of Lisburne in Ireland.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to amend several Acts relating to the Coasting Trade of Great Britain.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to enable the Commissioners or Governors of Greenwich Hospital to continue to provide for the Payment of Out Pensioners of the said Hospital.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act for regulating the Exportation of Hops to Foreign Parts, and allowing a Drawback of the Excise Duty paid thereon.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to extend to Ireland an Act of the last Session of Parliament, for granting an additional Bounty on the Exportation of certain Silk Manufactures, and to continue the same until the Fifth Day of July One thousand eight hundred and twenty two.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act for altering the Drawback on Acetous Acid exported; and for exempting Tiles made for draining Lands from Duty.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p01] An Act to authorize Collectors of the Customs in Ireland to bring to Account the Proceeds of Goods sold under the Provisions of the Warehousing Acts.
