[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] An Act for amending and repairing the Road from Thirsk, over Skipton Bridge, to Hutton Moor, and through Ainderby, Quernhow and Nosterfield, to Masham in the North Riding of the County of York.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] passed for repairing the Road from the Borough of Leicester, in the County of Leicester, to the Town of Ashby de la Zouch, in the said County.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] for repairing the Roads from the Borough of Leicester, in the County of Leicester, to the Town of Narborough; and from the said Borough of Leicester to the Town of Earl Shilton, and from the said Town of Earl Shilton to the Town of Hinckley, in the said County.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] An Act for more effectually repairing the Road from Summerrod's Bar, near Hexham, in the County of Northumberland, to Alston, in the County of Cumberland.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] for repairing the High Road from the Borough of Ripon, by Ingram Bank, to the Town of Pateley Bridge, in the County of York.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] An Act for repairing the Roads from Stratford upon Avon in the County of Warwick, through Alcester and Feckenham, to Bradley Brook in the County of Worcester, and other Roads therein mentioned in the same Counties.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] An Act for more effectually making, repairing and improving the Roads from the Town of Lewes through Off ham to Witch Cross, from the Cliffe near Lewes aforesaid through Uckfield to Witch Cross aforesaid, and from the Cliffe aforesaid to Burwash, all in the County of Sussex.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] An Act for more effectually repairing and amending the Roads from Liverpool to Prescot, Ashton and Warrington, and other Roads therein mentioned, in the County Palatine of Lancaster.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] for repairing and widening the Road from Skipton, to the Turnpike Road leading from Leeds to Ripon, near Ockbeck, in the Township of Bilton with Harrogate, and from thence to communicate with the Road leading from Knaresborough to Wetherby, in the West Riding of the County of York.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] for repairing the Roads leading from Wades Mill, in the County of Hertford, to Barley and Royston, in the said County.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] An Act for more effectually repairing and improving the Roads from Hurdlow House, through Buxton in the County of Derby, and Stockport in the County Palatine of Chester, to Manchester in the County Palatine of Lancaster, and other Roads therein mentioned, in the said Counties.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] for keeping in Repair several Roads leading from the Town of Ivelchester, in the County of Somerset.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] for repairing the Road from Denbigh to Saint Asaph, and from thence to Ruthland, in the Counties of Denbigh and Flint.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] An Act to enable the Vestrymen of the Parish of Saint Mary le bone, in the County of Middlesex, to effectuate the building of Four District Churches in the said Parish, and for other Purposes relating thereto.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] An Act for establishing a proper Place for holding Markets and Fairs for the Sale of Live Stock in the City of Gloucester and the Suburbs thereof, and for opening convenient Avenues thereto, and for watching and otherwise improving the said City.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] An Act for more effectually converting into Money the Statute Labour of the County of Sutherland, and for more effectually making and maintaining Roads therein, to which the Statute Labour is applicable, and increasing the Amount of Bridge Money leviable within the same.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] for building a new Parish Church and Chapel for the said Parish.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] An Act for more effectually repairing the Roads leading from Henley Bridge, in the County of Oxford, to Dorchester Bridge, and from thence to Culham Bridge, and to a Place called Milestone, in the Road leading to Magdalen Bridge, in the said County.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] An Act for more effectually making, repairing and improving the Road from near the Place where the Broil Park Gate formerly stood to the Horsebridge Turnpike Road on the Dicker, and from the Blacksmith's Shop in Horsebridge Street to the Town of Battle, in the County of Sussex.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] for making and repairing certain Roads in the Counties of Fife, Kinross, Perth and Clackmannan.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] for more effectually repairing the Road from Foston Bridge, in the County of Lincoln, to Little Drayton in the County of Nottingham.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] An Act for more effectually repairing and improving the Road from Newark upon Trent, in the County of Nottingham, to join the Road from Nottingham to Grantham, in the County of Lincoln, near the Guide Post on the Foss Road, near Bingham, in the said County of Nottingham.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] An Act for repairing and improving the Road from Skipton in the County of York, to Clitheroe in the County of Lancaster.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] for repairing the Road from Newport, in the County of Salop, to Welsh Harp, in the Township of Stonnall, in the County of Stafford.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] passed for making and maintaining a Road from the Romford and Whitechapel Road, to or near Tilbury Fort, in the County of Essex.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] An Act for repairing and maintaining the Roads leading from Spalding High Bridge, through Littleworth, and by Frognall, to James Deeping Stone Bridge, in the County of Lincoln, and thence to Maxey Outgang, in the County of Northampton, adjoining the High Road there.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] Years of the Reign of His late Majesty King George the Third, so far as the same relate to the Road from Alfold Bars, in the County of Surrey, to Newbridge, in the County of Sussex.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] for repairing the Roads leading to and from the City of Exeter, and for making a new Branch of Road to communicate therewith.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] passed for repairing the Road leading from Burleigh Bridge in Loughborough, to Ashby de la Zouch, in the County of Leicester; and also the Road branching out of the said Road at Coleorton Church, to Rempstone, in the Counties of Leicester and Nottingham.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] for repairing the Road leading from the High Street in the City of Rochester, to Maidstone, in the County of Kent; and for amending and improving the Road branching from the said Road, at the Bridgewood Gates, and running into the Town of Chatham, in the said County of Kent.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] An Act for more effectually repairing and improving the Road leading from Flimwell Vent, in the Parish of Ticehurst, in the County of Sussex, to the Town and Port of Hastings, in the said County.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] for constructing an Harbour in Mount's Bay, in the County of Cornwall.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] An Act to remove Doubts as to the Power of the Commissioners of Exchequer Bills to advance a further Sum of Money to the Regent's Canal Company, and to amend the Acts for making the said Canal.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] An Act for making and maintaining a Railway or Tramroad from the River Tees at Stockton, to Witton Park Colliery, with several Branches therefrom, all in the County of Durham.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] An Act for lighting with Gas the Town of Kingston upon Hull, and certain Places adjacent thereto.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] by several Acts relating to the said Navigation.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] passed for more effectually supplying with Water the Inhabitants of the Towns of Manchester and Salford, in the Parish of Manchester, in the County Palatine of Lancaster; and for further extending the Powers and Provisions of the said Acts.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] for paving, lighting and cleansing the Streets, and for regulating the Police of the City of Glasgow.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] An Act for incorporating the City of Coventry Gas Light Company.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p02] An Act for incorporating the South London Gas Light and Coke Company, situate in the Parish of Saint Saviour, in the County of Surrey.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p03] An Act for lighting with Gas the Turnpike Road from Whitechapel Church in the County of Middlesex, to certain Dwelling Houses erected and being beyond the Four Mile Stones upon the Ilford and Woodford Roads, in the County of Essex.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p03] An Act for more effectually making, maintaining and repairing certain Roads in the County of Aberdeen, and in the Counties of Banff and Kincardine.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p03] for inclosing Lands in the Manor of Lambeth, in the County of Surrey.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p03] for repairing the Roads from Sheet Bridge to Portsmouth, and from Petersfield to the Alton Turnpike Road, near Ropley, in the County of Southampton.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p03] An Act for lighting with Gas the Town of Newport, in the Isle of Wight, and Places adjacent.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p03] for paving, lighting and watching the Town of Shrewsbury, in the County of Salop; and for granting other Powers in lieu thereof.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p03] An Act for erecting the Town of Airdrie, in the County of Lanark, into a Burgh of Barony, paving, lighting and improving the same, and establishing a Police therein.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p03] An Act to enable the Company of Proprietors of the Stratford upon Avon Canal Navigation, to subscribe a further Sum of Money for the Purposes of the said Navigation.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p03] An Act for giving further Powers to the Company of Proprietors of the River Arun Navigation, and for confirming certain Agreements entered into between the said Company, and the Company of Proprietors of the Portsmouth and Arundel Navigation.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p03] An Act for making and maintaining a Railway or Tramroad from Stratford upon Avon in the County of Warwick to Moreton in Marsh in the County of Gloucester, with a Branch to Shipston upon Stour in the County of Worcester.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p03] for improving the Drainage of the Middle and South Levels, Part of the Great Level of the Fens called Bedford Level, and other Lands therein mentioned, and for improving the Navigation of the River Ouze, in the County of Norfolk, and of the several Rivers communicating therewith.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p03] An Act to enable the Justices of the Peace for the County of Brecon to rebuild repair and take down Bridges within the said County not being County Bridges.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p03] An Act for enabling the Proprietors of the Commercial Buildings, in the Town of Belfast, to sue and be sued in the Name of their Secretary, and for the Regulation of the said Buildings, and the Property thereof.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p03] An Act for better lighting and for watching the City of Chichester, and Places adjacent.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p03] An Act for supplying the Towns of Old and New Brentford, and the Villages of Turnham Green, Hammersmith and Kensington, in the County of Middlesex, with Gas.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p03] An Act for incorporating the Town of Dudley Gas Light Company.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p03] An Act to light and otherwise improve the Streets and other Public Passages and Places within the Hamlet of Mile End Old Town, in the Parish of Saint Dunstan, Stepney, otherwise Stebonheath, in the County of Middlesex.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p03] An Act for incorporating the Town of Portsea Gas Light Company.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p03] An Act for lighting the Town of Barnsley, in the West Riding of the County of York, with Gas.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p03] An Act for lighting with Gas the Town and Borough of Ipswich, in the County of Suffolk.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p03] An Act for providing an Increase of the Annual Income of the London Institution.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p03] for amending the Road leading from the South End of the Moor Lane, in the Township of Great Bolton, into the Turnpike Road from Manchester to Wigan, near Westhoughton Chapel, in the County Palatine of Lancaster.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p03] for repairing the Roads from Keyberry Bridge to Shalldon, and from the said Bridge to Torquay, in the County of Devon; and to alter the Line of certain Parts of the said Roads.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p03] An Act for repairing the Road from Birmingham through Stratford upon Avon to Stratford Bridge in the County of Warwick.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p03] An Act for repairing Part of the Great Road from Gloucester to Bristol, and certain Roads through and near the Towns of Berkeley, Dursley, Wotton under Edge and Stroud, and other Roads therein mentioned, in the Counties of Gloucester and Wilts.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p03] An Act for repairing the Roads from Tetbury to Symondshall, from Frocester Hill to Dunkirk, and from the Latterwood to Nailsworth, and other Roads therein mentioned, all in the County of Gloucester.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p03] An Act for repairing the Road from Alemouth through Alnwick and Rothbury to Hexham, and a Branch from the said Road between Alnwick and Rothbury to Jockey's Dike Bridge, all in the County of Northumberland.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p03] An Act for amending and more effectually repairing the Highway between Hockliffe and Woburn, in the County of Bedford; and for repairing the Road leading through Woburn to Tickford Bridge, in Newport Pagnell, in the County of Buckingham.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p03] for repairing the Road from the Turnpike Road near the Town of Weston on the Green, in the County of Oxford, to the Turnpike Road on Kidlington Green, in the said County.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p03] for repairing and keeping in Repair the Road from Parkhouse to or near the Three Mile House, in the County of Lanark.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p03] An Act for amending and keeping in Repair the several Roads leading to and from the late Market House in Stourbridge, in the County of Worcester, and also several other Roads leading from and connected with the said Roads in the Counties of Worcester and Stafford.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p03] for repairing and widening several Roads leading from the Town of Bewdley, in the County of Worcester, to the several Places therein mentioned, in the Counties of Worcester and Salop respectively.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p03] An Act for making a Road from Bury, in the County Palatine of Lancaster, to or near a certain House, known by the Sign of The Bull and Wharf, in the Township of Little Bolton, in the said County.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p03] An Act for more effectually repairing several Roads leading from Kidderminster, in the County of Worcester, and several other Roads connected therewith, in the Counties of Worcester, Stafford and Salop.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p04] An Act for repairing and maintaining several Roads leading from the Town of Bromyard, in the County of Hereford, and other Roads adjoining thereto, in the said County, and in the County of Worcester.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p04] for repairing the Road from Elsdon High Cross, near the Town of Elsdon, in the County of Northumberland, to the Red Swyre, upon the Mid Border betwixt England and Scotland.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p04] An Act for amending the Road from Leeds to Otley, in the West Riding of the County of York.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p04] An Act for providing a convenient House, with suitable Accommodations for His Majesty's Judges at the Assizes for the County of Salop, and for maintaining and supporting the same.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p04] An Act for more effectually enlarging, deepening, improving and maintaining the Harbour of Saltcoats, in the County of Ayr.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p04] An Act for improving and maintaining the Harbour Pier or Cobb, at the Port and Borough of Lyme Regis, in the County of Dorset.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p04] passed for repairing the Road from Coleham Bridge, in Shrewsbury, to the Market Place in Church Stretton, and several other Roads therein described, all in the County of Salop.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p04] An Act for building an additional Gaol for the county of Essex, and for enlarging, improving and altering the existing Prisons for the same County.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p04] An Act for making the Townships and Hamlets of Tarleton, and of Hesketh with Becconsall, in the Parish of Croston, and Part of the Rectory and Vicarage thereof, in the County of Lancaster, separate and distinct Parishes.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p04] for paving, lighting, and otherwise improving the Town of Ipswich, in the County of Suffolk.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p04] An Act for enclosing Lands in the Parish of Cley next the Sea, in the County of Norfolk; and for embanking and draining Parts of the said Lands, and Lands in the Parish of Wiveton, in the said County.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p04] for repairing the Road from Dundalk, in the County of Louth, to Bannbridge, in the County of Down, so far as relates to the Northern Division of the said Road.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p04] An Act for more effectually repairing the Road from Dunstable, in the County of Bedford, to the Pond Yards in the County of Hertford.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p04] An Act for repairing, widening and maintaining several Roads in the Counties of Dorset and Devon, leading to and through the Borough of Lyme Regis, and from the Turnpikę Road on Uplyme Hill, to the Turnpike Road at the Three Ashes, in the Parish of Crewkerne, in the County of Somerset.
[src:airdrie-north-lanarkshire/1-2-geo-4-p04] so far as relates to the Roads from the Top of Crickley Hill, in the County of Gloucester, to and through Northleach, Burford and Witney, to Campsfield, and the Turnpike Road at or near Enslow Bridge, in the County of Oxford.
